description: Latin superstrūctus, past participle of superstruō (“to build upon”); super (“over”) + struō (“to build”). See super- and structure.

verbs.description: superstruct (third-person singular simple present superstructs, present participle superstructing, simple past and past participle superstructed)

entries.meaning: To build over or upon (another structure); to erect upon (a foundation).
examples: This is the only proper basis on which to superstruct first innocency and then virtue.
